- goal
    - a python based approach to create wall art based on the world map or other maps
- projects
    [ ] a wall art map of the world, topographic map of the world, high res that can be printed on a full size wall, 
        - output should be in multiple formats to allow printing. 
        - It should allow for color palleted changes to adjust to people's needs. 
        - It should also allow selecting certain "country", "continent" or even a province/state/region/county where the rest of it are "cut out", i.e. they are not visible, like transparent png style where when printed only the "wall" shows.
    [ ] an interactive way to enter the coordinates of a "lake", "mountain", "city", "neighborhood", or just the names of them, find them, show their map (zoomable in and out) to the user to verify it is the right one, or show multiples on the map so that the user can select the one they are looking for, and then finding an appropriate "frame" for it, this should be done by letting user rotate, pan, zoom in and out on the map and draw an arbitrary rectangle to get the frame they want. Then creating a "topographic" map of it with "n" layers of countours where n is given by the user, default to 5. initially the distance between the layers is equal, for example if the lowest point is 1000m high and the highest is 2000m high, and n = 6, then we have 1000, 1200, 1400, 1600, 1800, and 2000. but later there sshould be a "slider" with 4 sliders on it that allows user to wiggle those middle ones to other values. of course this depends on the "available" hights in the data for that area and granularity. This means we need to find an open source data to get the altitudes for any location on earth. The output should be be multiple ways: svg files of vectors of different heights that can be fed to a cnc machine to just cut them directly at different heights or one layer each (let the user chose what they want). Also just pdf files of the contour lines, also "color coded" version of the pdf file or png/tiff/etc extensions with high quality (also let user decide about the quality). Have a few sensible pallets. for example for a lake or next to ocean having a blue shade pallet makes sense, for mountains green + brown + white, etc. and then also have a place where user can chose the colors and see the result change live. This interaction should be very smooth for the user.